    <stitle>ANTILOCK MODULATOR ASSEMBLY: BENDIX M-21 AND M-22 - OPERATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>OPERATION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="1">
            <title>NON-ANTILOCK APPLICATION</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0403003">Figure 3</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0403003" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0403003" filename="../figg04/G0403003.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Non-Antilock Application</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>During normal non-antilock braking, both solenoids are de-energized (no electrical power). Brake
                application air enters the Supply port of the modulator and flows to, and through, the open exhaust
                solenoid then to the exhaust diaphragm. Air pressure, along with spring force, seats the exhaust
                diaphragm on the exhaust passage, thus preventing the escape of service air. Simultaneously, application
                air flows to the supply diaphragm and forces it away from its seat. Air flows past the open supply and
                out the modulator delivery port to the service brake chambers.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
